
To add a remote branch,

  $ git remote add <remote_name> <HTTPS/SSH link>
  $ git pull <remote_name> <branch_name>
  
Now, if your local branch and remote branch get diverged,
to merge the remote branch into local,

  $ git pull <remote_name> <branch_name>
  
A window will appear with a suggested commit message. Edit
as per your wish or keep it as it is. Then 

  press Ctrl+C+O
  
Now, a suggested file name will be shown. Keep it or edit
it. Then

  press Enter
  press Ctrl+X
  
It will merge.
